org.omg.CORBA
Class SetOverrideType

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--org.omg.CORBA.SetOverrideType
All Implemented Interfaces:
IDLEntity, Serializable
public class SetOverrideType
extends Object
implements IDLEntity

The mapping of a CORBA enum tagging SET_OVERRIDE and ADD_OVERRIDE, which indicate whether policies should replace the existing policies of an Object or be added to them.

The method omg.org.CORBA.Object._set_policy_override takes either SetOverrideType.SET_OVERRIDE or SetOverrideType.ADD_OVERRIDE as its second argument. The method _set_policy_override creates a new Object initialized with the Policy objects supplied as the first argument. If the second argument is ADD_OVERRIDE, the new policies are added to those of the Object instance that is calling the _set_policy_override method. If SET_OVERRIDE is given instead, the existing policies are replaced with the given ones.

Since:
JDK1.2
